definitions.definition: A kind of coarse woollen cloth or stuff with a shaggy or tufted ( friezed ) nap on one side .

main_definition: A kind of coarse woollen cloth or stuff with a shaggy or tufted ( friezed ) nap on one side .

definitions.definition: That part of the entablature of an order which is between the architrave and cornice . It is a flat member or face, either uniform or broken by triglyphs , and often enriched with figures and other ornaments of sculpture.
Any sculptured or richly ornamented band in a building or, by extension, in rich pieces of furniture.
A banner with a series of pictures .
examples: The classroom had an alphabet frieze that showed an animal for each letter.
